{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"case"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"ammunition"}],"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"discussion","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Discussion"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If you use a weapon that has the ammunition property to make a melee"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"attack, you treat the weapon as an improvised weapon (see “Improvised"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Weapons” later in the section). A sling must be loaded to deal any damage"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"when used in this way."}]}]}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":2,"patch":0},"sections":[],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/dndengine\/dndweaponproperty\/ammunition"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/DnDEngine\/documentation\/DnDEngine\/DnDWeaponProperty\/ammunition","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"You can use a weapon that has the ammunition property to make a ranged"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"attack only if you have ammunition to fire from the weapon. Each time you"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"attack with the weapon, you expend one piece of ammunition. Drawing the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"ammunition from a quiver, case, or other container is part of the attack"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"(you need a free hand to load a one-handed weapon). At the end of the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"battle, you can recover half your expended ammunition by taking a minute"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"to search the battlefield."}],"kind":"symbol","metadata":{"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"case"},{"kind":"text","